Given are the terms used in this project:
Cell: A single button/ grid box in the grid. Can hold a maximum of three units.
Units: An entity which is owned by a player and placed in the cell when the player clicks
on the cell, or as the result of a reaction.
Critical mass: The maximum number of units a cell can hold without exploding.
Explosion: The process of an unstable cell releasing the number of units equal to critical mass 
for the cell+1.
Critical mass for cells at the edge=2, corner=1, center=3.
Cells are the fundamental units in the board